                  Essential Commands



            Command        |       Description
_________________________________________________
                    
Directories:        
                           |
$ pwd                      | Display path of current working directory
$ mkdir <directory>        | Change directory to <directory>
$ rmdir <directory>        | Deletes Directory
$ cd <directory>           | Create new directory <directory>
$ cd ..                    | Change to parent directory
$ ls                       | List contents
$ ls -la                   | List detailed and hidden contents
                           |
Files:

$ touch <file>             | Create <file> 
$ rm <file>                | Delete <file>
$ rm -r <file>             | Delete <directory>
$ rm -f <file>             | Force-delete <file>
$ mv <oldfile> <newfile>   | rename <oldfile> to <newfile>
$ cp <file> <directory>    | Move <file> to <directory>
$ cp -r <directory1> <dir2>| Copy <directory1> contents to <dir2>
                           |
Output:

$ cat <file>               | Output the contents of <file>
$ less <file>              | Output the contents of <file> 
$ head <file>              | Output first ten lines of <file>
$ <cmd> <file>             | Direct output of <cmd> to <file>
$ <cmd> >> <file>          | Append output of <cmd> to <file>
$ clear                    | Clear the command line window
                           |
Search:

$ find <dir> -name "<file>"| Find files named <file> in <dir>
$ grep "<text>" <file>     | Output instances of <text> in file
$ grep -rl "<text>" <dir>  | Search for all files containing <text> in <dir>
                           |

Permissions:

$ chmod UGO + RWX <file>   | Add read, write and execute permissions to user, group and others for <file>
$ chmod -R ... <dir>       | Change permissions of <dir> and contents
$ chown <user> <file>      | Change ownership of <file> to <user>
                           |

More:

$ ps ax                    | Output currently running processes
$ whoami                   | Outputs username of current user
$ wc                       | Word count, -l(lines), -w(words), -c(byte size)
$ man <cmd>                | shows manual for <cmd>
$ date                     | View & modify time
$ env                      | Output list of environment variables

